Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveThe Catholic Bishop of Enugu Diocese, Bishop Calistus Onaga, has barred Catholics from attending the Adoration Ministry of Father Ejike Mbaka.
In a letter he personally signed on Friday, Bishop Onaga said the prohibition subsists until due canonical processes are concluded.
Part of the letter read, “I hereby prohibit all Catholics (clergy, religious and lay faithful) henceforth from attending all religious and liturgical activities of the Catholic Adoration Ministry until the due canonical process initiated by the Diocese is concluded.”
Mbaka had been trending over his comments on the presidential candidate of the Labour Party, Peter Obi
